  "bio": [
    "Chris Ruddy is the founder and CEO of Boca Raton, Florida-based conservative news outlet Newsmax.",
    "He founded Newsmax in 1998 with a $25,000 investment from Mellon banking fortune heir Richard Mellon Scaife (d. 2014).",
    "Newsmax went public on the New York Stock Exchange in March 2025; Ruddy owns nearly a third of the company's shares.",
    "Ruddy launched Newsmax's cable news channel in 2014. In 2024, it was the fourth-largest news channel in the U.S. with 30 million regular viewers.",
    "Newsmax also has an online news site, a news app, a paid subscription and streaming service called Newsmax Plus and two print publications."
  ],
  "about": [
    "Ruddy worked as a journalist at the New York Post and the Pittsburgh Tribune-Review before launching Newsmax."
